<TITLE> Bangladesh face Afghanistan in SA Games football final </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 5 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh reached the final of the 11th South Asian Games men's football competition after knocking out arch-rivals India by a solitary goal at the Bangabandhu National Stadium on Friday. Substitute forward Touhidul Alam Sobuj struck the winner in the 85th minute. The hosts will face Afghanistan in Monday's final. Afghanistan defeated the Maldives in the second semi-final with a 72nd minute goal by Belal Arezou in a physical contest which saw both sides reduced to 10 men. Bangladesh's golden moment arrived when Komol unleashed a fierce grounder from the top of the box that bounced out of a diving Gurpreet Singh's grip and unmarked Sobuj kept his cool to slot home with a neat left footed placing shot to ignite wild celebrations throughout the stadium. Twenty20 cricket Bangladesh will play Sri Lanka in the final of the inaugural Twenty20 cricket competition after registering a 52-run victory against Pakistan at the Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium. The final is on Sunday. Chasing 157 to win, Pakistan could only manage 104 in 17.3 overs with Nayyar Abbas (37) and Ali Asad (17) reaching double figures. Pacer Shuvashis Roy, Nasir Hossain and Sanjamul Islam claimed two wickets each respectively while Nazmul Islam, Sabbir Rahman and Asif Ahmed took one wicket each. Earlier, the hosts made 156-6 after winning the toss. Sabbir Rahman scored 46 featuring two fours and four sixes while Nasir Hossain contributed a 43-ball 45 with four boundaries. Hockey Bangladesh missed a chance to play in the hockey final after India came back from a 2-0 first half deficit, to salvage a 3-3 draw at the Maulana Bhasani National Stadium. Kamruzzaman and Pushkar Khisha scored one goal each for Bangladesh to give the hosts a 2-0 lead before the break. But India scored three goals through V Raghunath, Mohammad Aamir and Dharamveer Singh in the second half to dash Bangladesh's hopes. Golam Mustafa scored a last-gasp goal to force a draw. India will face Pakistan in the 